Calling a DLL using Microsft

    This examples shows how to call a Microsoft 32-bit PE DLL from a 
    Microsoft 32-bit PE program.  The example uses the DOS/4G API to 
    load the DLL using either of two methods: an IMPLIB, to cause the 
    DLL to be loaded at program load time, or dynamically, using the 
    DOS/4G D32LoadModule API call.

    The example consists of the following files in the EXAMPLES\DLL\MICROSFT
    directory:

    MYDLL.C     C source for DLL example code.
    
    CALLER.C    C source file for calling DLL functions in MYDLL.

    MAKEFILE    Polymake-configured makefile to build all the example
                executables using Watcom.
